It’s been a year since Gasparilla and my Solo Show and that’s really crazy! I spent so much time and energy focusing on those things that I got little burned out to say the least. Save for a project here and there, I have slowed down considerably in the art arena. I have been focusing a ton on teaching myself digital art, because it is something I always wanted to do, but this is just a throw back to my 18 hour days/7 days a week! 😂

🎨✂️✨🔍 Recently, I've been captivated by the process of creating intricate collages by cutting and layering paper. 📌🖼️ Prototyping allows me to refine my vision, experimenting with different arrangements and techniques until the artwork comes to life just as I imagined. 🌟 Embracing the joy of discovering new methods, I've found that each snip and layer unveils a world of creative possibilities. 🌈✨ #ArtisticPrototyping #Collage #UnveilingCreativity

🌈 🎨💫 Vibrant hues blending into harmony, to contrasting elements creating beautiful tensions, this journey has been a captivating dive into the art of juxtaposition. 🖼️ Embracing the balance between light and shadow, chaos and order, and the endless possibilities that emerge when two worlds collide. 🌌 Let your imagination run wild and discover the magic that arises when colors and contrasts unite! ✨🔳🔲 #ColorCollageDuality #ArtisticExploration #VibrantContrasts
🎨🌈 Obsessed with the interplay of colors and the magic of layering, I'm on a journey. 🎨🖌️ #ColorObsession #LayeredArtistry #ArtisticJourney

When the world feels grey, creating with color can provide a sense of control, a way to reclaim a piece of joy. It's a reminder that we create our own realities.
